                        <div class="info-para">
                            <div class="header-block">
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    Stroke is an emergency medical condition due to disturbed blood supply to the brain
                                    It can also be called “Brain Attack” in common language to denote significance like “Heart Attack”
                                    There are two types of stroke :
                                </p>
                                <ol class="block-listing">
                                    <li>Ischemic Stroke (Due to blood clotting in the brain)</li>
                                    <li>Hemorrhagic Stroke / Brain hemorrhage ( Due to Bleeding in the brain)Hemorrhagic Stroke / Brain hemorrhage ( Due to Bleeding in the brain)</li>
                                </ol>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    Emergency treatment in the “Golden Hours” (First 4.5 hours of stroke ) is important. Early treatment of clotting type of stroke is by giving blood thinners and removing clot by a surgery through arteries (Thrombectomy).
                                    Treatment of Brain haemorrhage is by controlling blood pressure, brain swelling and reversing brain bleed. Some patients need life saving surgery. If patient can get this timely treatment, then their brain and life can be saved.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    Hence it is important to reach a “Stroke ready Hospital” as early as possible after stroke
                                    Stroke symptoms can be remembered by the phrase <strong>BE FAST</strong>
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    <strong>
                                        B (Balance): Loss of Balance<br />
                                        E (Eyes): Vision loss or blurring of vision<br />
                                        F (Face): Drooping of face on one side<br />
                                        A (Arm): Inability raise arm<br />
                                        S (Speech): Slurring of Speech<br />
                                        T (Time): Time to reach hospital at the earliest
                                    </strong>
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    If someone around you is experiencing these symptoms, they should be taken to a stroke ready hospital at the earliest.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    Risk factors for stroke are Advanced age, Hypertension, Diabetes, Heart Disease, Smoking, Alcohol consumption, Lack of Exercise, High cholesterol, diseases of blood clotting and diseases of blood vessels.
                                </p>
                                <p class="profile-position">
                                    To reduce the risk of stroke it is important to regularly check and control blood pressure, blood glucose and bad cholesterol. Quitting smoking and alcohol, healthy diet and regular exercise are also crucial.
                                </p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
