                                    Epilepsy is a condition due to abnormal electrical activity in the brain. It presents in many forms suck as jerky movements of arms or legs, deviation of mouth, unrolling of eyeballs, frothing from mouth, tongue bite, incontinence, loss of consciousness and impairment of attention. The episodes are called as “Seizures” or “Fits”. They can last from seconds to minutes. Repeated seizures can result in a life threatening emergency. For patients experiencing such episodes, it is important to visit a Neurologist. Your Neurologist will take a detailed  history, conduct a Neurologic Examination and do certain investigations. The diagnosis is made after a complete workup and patient is started on treatment. It is important for the patients to take medicines regularly. They should avoid activities such as swimming and driving till the time their seizures are well controlled.
                                </p>
