                                    Headache is a common Neurologic problem. Most of the headaches are benign and self limited. Few patients have headache due to underlying brain diseases (Secondary Headache). These problems can be detected by a Brain Scan. But most of the patients do not have any brain diseases identifiable on the scan. Such cases are Called Primary Headaches. Common types of such headache are Migraine, Tension type Headache and Cluster Headache. By a detailed history and clinical assessment, the Neurologist makes diagnosis of headache type and appropriate treatment is started. Migraine headache can be on one side or both sids of head. Some patients can also have other features such as nausea, vomitting, vision symptoms, dizziness, transient loss of consciousness, speech and language issues, neck pain and shoulder pain. The migraine attacks can last from hours to days. The treatment consists of medicines for relief from attacks and preventing the attacks. Measures to prevent migraine attacks include maintaining a healthy lifestyle, regular exercise, healthy diet, regular sleep schedule, avoiding smoking and alcohol.
                                </p>
