                                    Neck and Back pain are one of the commonest conditions for which a Neurologist is consulted. Sometimes neck pain can be associated with pain and tingling in the arm. Similarly, back pain can be associated with pain and tingling in the legs. If the pain symptoms are associated with other concerning features such as loss of sensation, loss of power for lack of control over urination, then you should immediately visit a Neurologist. The evaluation requires detailed clinical assessment and scans in some cases. Most common cause is degenerative condition such as spondylosis. Other causes include slip disc, nutritional, inflammatory or traumatic conditions. The treatment is according to cause and it includes medicines and physiotherapy. Some patients may need surgery if nerve root or spinal cord compression is significant. To prevent neck or back pain, regular exercise, maintaining health diet and maintaining correct neck and back posture are essential.
