                                    Spinal cord diseases are of two types: Compressive and Noncompressive. Compressive diseases are due to compression of spinal cord due to diseases of vertebral column, tumours, infections or trauma. Noncompressive spinal cord diseases are due to nutritional, infective, autoimmune, inflammatory or traumatic conditions affecting spinal cord. The spinal cord disorders can present with pain, numbness, tingling, loss of power, difficulty in standing and walking, loss of urinary control. A careful assessment by Neurologist is essential for diagnosing type of spinal cord disorder. Depending on type of spinal cord disorder, treatment includes medical management, surgical management and physiotherapy.
                                </p>
